1883432b-d89f-4438-971a-8d136eeed31b.0bb853c3-4966-4232-ac53-c3345a631450.prompt=Enter a value for eventid 1883432b-d89f-4438-971a-8d136eeed31b.0f093827-4cc5-4955-b433-2c45961b7271.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

1883432b-d89f-4438-971a-8d136eeed31b.3d600a46-1609-41be-a724-8844fbf4f47a.prompt=Enter a value for host 1883432b-d89f-4438-971a-8d136eeed31b.69796627-065b-4714-b052-440ea6dab299.prompt=Enter a value for age 1883432b-d89f-4438-971a-8d136eeed31b.77d62aeb-663b-4ffc-8ec7-a139fa537397.description=
Searches the NT Event Log using the supplied search criteria.

Inputs\:
host - The hostname or ip address of the machine you want to search against.
user - Username to use for WMI impersonation on the host for this operation (to be left blank for localhost).
password - Password of the user.
log - The name of the Event Log to search. Example\: Application or System or Security or *.
age - The number of seconds old an event can be to be counted.  Use * for all.
severity - The severity of the event.  Use * for all. Valid values\: error, information, warning, *.
threshold - The value used to determine the response.
eventid - The eventid of the event.
source - The source of the event.
message - The message text of the searched events. If left empty the search will not consider the message.

Responses\:
over threshold - The number of events found was higher than the input parameter threshold or equal to it.
under threshold - The number of events found was lower than the input parameter threshold.
host not found - Host could not be resolved.
Invalid parameters - An unknown Error occurred.

Extra Results\:
count - The total number of events that matched.
logs - The actual logs captured.

Notes\: 
1. The username and password inputs must be blank for localhost and fully qualified usernames must be used for remote hosts.
Example\:
user\: DOMAIN\Administrator
password\: password

2. If a hostname is assigned to the host input, please make sure that the DNS Server you have set is correct, otherwise the hostname will not be resolved.
1883432b-d89f-4438-971a-8d136eeed31b.81a69c14-ff78-4cff-91ed-af7fcccd6217.description=
Adds a value into the global context (available to all parent and child flows)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
1883432b-d89f-4438-971a-8d136eeed31b.82379feb-dc3e-450a-ba48-54f811c9b14b.description=
Executes an Expression (e.x value1 \=\= value2)

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the value to threshold with
value2 - the threshold to threshold against
operator - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
okstring - string to push into returnResult if the threshold has not been passed
failedstring - string to push into the returnResult if the threshold has been passed

Responses\:
true - the expression is true
fales - the expression is false
1883432b-d89f-4438-971a-8d136eeed31b.8be25e87-5a96-4fe7-9110-a704bb069123.description=

1883432b-d89f-4438-971a-8d136eeed31b.description=
Checks if a number of events in an event log exceeds a threshold, and recommends action if they do.
      
      inputs\:
threshold - A threshold to compare the measuredValue against..
Threshold function - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
diagnostic name - the name of this diagnostic.
diagnostic so far - The output of previous diagnostics, used for chaining diagnostics together.
recommended resolution - A recommendation for resolving the problem if the measured value is outside the threshold.
host - hostname or ip address of the machine you want to search against
log - the name of the Event Log to search (ex. Application or System or Security or *)
source - the source of the event
eventid - the eventid of the event
severity - (error, information, warning, *) the severity of the event.  Use * for all
message - the message text of the event (this input requires a regular expressions)
age - (value, *) the number of seconds old an event can be to be counted.  Use * for all
threshold - the value used to determine the response
username - user account to use to connect to machine
password - password for user account
     
responses\:
success - Measured values were below threshold.
diagnosed - Measured Values were above threshold.
failure - Something went wrong.
flow.name: Windows Event Log Diagnostic

staticBinding.value: ${diagnostic name} was outside of threshold. Number of events found was: ${measuredValue} Threshold was ${threshold}. The recommended procedure for resolving this issue is: ${recommended resolution}
${diagnostic name} Failed to run because there was an error checking the event logs.
